{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop the Houses of Parliament renovation: Spend it on our NHS instead",
        "additional_details": "In our view, the possible \u00a339.2bn cost is an insult to taxpayers during a national crisis. We are told \"there is no money,\" yet billions are found for a Victorian relic. We believe that common sense must prevail over sentimentality, and that a purpose-built building could save tens of billions and be more efficient. The British people should not bankroll a multi-billion-pound fossil while our hospitals and schools are crumbling. Put public need before old stones.",
        "background": "Cancel the \"Restoration and Renewal\" program. Instead of spending up to \u00a339bn on the Houses of Parliament (Palace of Westminster), the Government should build a modern, cost-effective seat of democracy for a fraction of the cost. Savings must be diverted to the NHS and public services.",
